41struct VarDecl
42{
43 explicit VarDecl(const TVariable &var) : mVariable(&var), mIsField(false) {}
44 explicit VarDecl(const TField &field) : mField(&field), mIsField(true) {}
45
46 ANGLE_INLINE const TVariable &variable() const
47 {
48 ASSERT(isVariable());
49 return *mVariable;
50 }
51
52 ANGLE_INLINE const TField &field() const
53 {
54 ASSERT(isField());
55 return *mField;
56 }
57
58 ANGLE_INLINE bool isVariable() const { return !mIsField; }
59
60 ANGLE_INLINE bool isField() const { return mIsField; }
61
62 const TType &type() const { return isField() ? *field().type() : variable().getType(); }
63
64 SymbolType symbolType() const
65 {
66 return isField() ? field().symbolType() : variable().symbolType();
67 }
68
69 private:
70 union
71 {
72 const TVariable *mVariable;
73 const TField *mField;
74 };
75 bool mIsField;
76};

226void GenMetalTraverser::emitIndentation()
227{
228 ASSERT(mIndentLevel >= 0);
229
230 if (mLastIndentationPos == mOut.size())
231 {
232 return; // Line is already indented.
233 }
234
235 for (int i = 0; i < mIndentLevel; ++i)
236 {
237 mOut << " ";
238 }
239
240 mLastIndentationPos = mOut.size();
241}
242
243void GenMetalTraverser::emitOpeningPointerParen()
244{
245 mOut << "(*";
246 mOpenPointerParenCount++;
247}
248
249void GenMetalTraverser::emitClosingPointerParen()
250{
251 if (mOpenPointerParenCount > 0)
252 {
253 mOut << ")";
254 mOpenPointerParenCount--;
255 }
256}

751 case TOperator::EOpPreIncrement:
752 case TOperator::EOpPreDecrement: {
753 return 3;
754 } break;
755
756 case TOperator::EOpPostIncrement:
757 case TOperator::EOpPostDecrement: {
758 return 2;
759 } break;
760
761 default: {
762 TODO();
763 return -1;
764 }
765 }

780static Associativity GetAssociativity(TOperator op)
781{
782 switch (op)
783 {
784 case TOperator::EOpAdd:
785 case TOperator::EOpSub:
786 case TOperator::EOpMul:
787 case TOperator::EOpDiv:
788 case TOperator::EOpIMod:
789 case TOperator::EOpBitShiftLeft:
790 case TOperator::EOpBitShiftRight:
791 case TOperator::EOpBitwiseAnd:
792 case TOperator::EOpBitwiseXor:
793 case TOperator::EOpBitwiseOr:
794 case TOperator::EOpEqual:
795 case TOperator::EOpNotEqual:
796 case TOperator::EOpLessThan:
797 case TOperator::EOpGreaterThan:
798 case TOperator::EOpLessThanEqual:
799 case TOperator::EOpGreaterThanEqual:
800 case TOperator::EOpLogicalOr:
801 case TOperator::EOpLogicalXor:
802 case TOperator::EOpLogicalAnd:
803 case TOperator::EOpComma: {
804 return Associativity::Left;
805 } break;
806
807 case TOperator::EOpAssign:
808 case TOperator::EOpInitialize:
809 case TOperator::EOpAddAssign:
810 case TOperator::EOpSubAssign:
811 case TOperator::EOpMulAssign:
812 case TOperator::EOpDivAssign:
813 case TOperator::EOpIModAssign:
814 case TOperator::EOpBitShiftLeftAssign:
815 case TOperator::EOpBitShiftRightAssign:
816 case TOperator::EOpBitwiseAndAssign:
817 case TOperator::EOpBitwiseXorAssign:
818 case TOperator::EOpBitwiseOrAssign: {
819 return Associativity::Right;
820 } break;
821
822 case TOperator::EOpNegative:
823 case TOperator::EOpPositive:
824 case TOperator::EOpLogicalNot:
825 case TOperator::EOpBitwiseNot:
826 case TOperator::EOpPostIncrement:
827 case TOperator::EOpPostDecrement:
828 case TOperator::EOpPreIncrement:
829 case TOperator::EOpPreDecrement: {
830 return Associativity::None;
831 } break;
832
833 default: {
834 TODO();
835 return Associativity::None;
836 }
837 }
838}

841static bool IsSymbolicOperator(TOperator op,
842 const TType &resultType,
843 const TType *argType0,
844 const TType *argType1 = nullptr)
845{
846 if (op == TOperator::EOpCallBuiltInFunction)
847 {
848 return false;
849 }
850 return !std::isalnum(GetOperatorString(op, resultType, argType0, argType1)[0]);
851}

853static TIntermBinary *AsSpecificBinaryNode(TIntermNode &node, TOperator op)
854{
855 TIntermBinary *binaryNode = node.getAsBinaryNode();
856 if (binaryNode)
857 {
858 return binaryNode->getOp() == op ? binaryNode : nullptr;
859 }
860 return nullptr;
861}
862
863static bool Parenthesize(TIntermNode &node)
864{
865 if (node.getAsSymbolNode())
866 {
867 return false;
868 }
869 if (node.getAsConstantUnion())
870 {
871 return false;
872 }
873 if (node.getAsAggregate())
874 {
875 return false;
876 }
877 if (node.getAsSwizzleNode())
878 {
879 return false;
880 }
881
882 if (TIntermUnary *unaryNode = node.getAsUnaryNode())
883 {
884 // TODO: Use a precedence and associativity rules instead of this ad-hoc impl.
885 const TType &resultType = unaryNode->getType();
886 const TType &argType = unaryNode->getOperand()->getType();
887 return IsSymbolicOperator(unaryNode->getOp(), resultType, &argType);
888 }
889
890 if (TIntermBinary *binaryNode = node.getAsBinaryNode())
891 {
892 // TODO: Use a precedence and associativity rules instead of this ad-hoc impl.
893 const TOperator op = binaryNode->getOp();
894 switch (op)
895 {
896 case TOperator::EOpIndexDirectStruct:
897 case TOperator::EOpIndexDirectInterfaceBlock:
898 case TOperator::EOpIndexDirect:
899 case TOperator::EOpIndexIndirect:
900 return Parenthesize(*binaryNode->getLeft());
901
902 case TOperator::EOpAssign:
903 case TOperator::EOpInitialize:
904 return AsSpecificBinaryNode(*binaryNode->getRight(), TOperator::EOpComma);
905
906 default:
907 {
908 const TType &resultType = binaryNode->getType();
909 const TType &leftType = binaryNode->getLeft()->getType();
910 const TType &rightType = binaryNode->getRight()->getType();
911 return IsSymbolicOperator(binaryNode->getOp(), resultType, &leftType, &rightType);
912 }
913 }
914 }
915
916 return true;
917}

929
930 if (emitParens)

1077void GenMetalTraverser::emitType(const TType &type, const EmitTypeConfig &etConfig)
1078{
1079 const bool isUBO = etConfig.evdConfig ? etConfig.evdConfig->isUBO : false;
1080 if (etConfig.evdConfig)
1081 {
1082 const auto &evdConfig = *etConfig.evdConfig;
1083 if (isUBO)
1084 {
1085 if (type.isArray())
1086 {
1087 mOut << "ANGLE_tensor<";
1088 }
1089 }
1090 if (evdConfig.isPointer)
1091 {
1092 mOut << toString(*evdConfig.isPointer);
1093 mOut << " ";
1094 }
1095 else if (evdConfig.isReference)
1096 {
1097 mOut << toString(*evdConfig.isReference);
1098 mOut << " ";
1099 }
1100 }
1101
1102 if (!isUBO)
1103 {
1104 if (type.isArray())
1105 {
1106 mOut << "ANGLE_tensor<";
1107 }
1108 }
1109
1110 if (type.isVector() || type.isMatrix())
1111 {
1112 mOut << "metal::";
1113 }
1114
1115 if (etConfig.evdConfig && etConfig.evdConfig->isPacked)
1116 {
1117 mOut << "packed_";
1118 }
1119
1120 emitBareTypeName(type, etConfig);
1121
1122 if (type.isVector())
1123 {
1124 mOut << type.getNominalSize();
1125 }
1126 else if (type.isMatrix())
1127 {
1128 mOut << type.getCols() << "x" << type.getRows();
1129 }
1130
1131 if (!isUBO)
1132 {
1133 if (type.isArray())
1134 {
1135 for (auto size : type.getArraySizes())
1136 {
1137 mOut << ", " << size;
1138 }
1139 mOut << ">";
1140 }
1141 }
1142
1143 if (etConfig.evdConfig)
1144 {
1145 const auto &evdConfig = *etConfig.evdConfig;
1146 if (evdConfig.isPointer)
1147 {
1148 mOut << " *";
1149 }
1150 else if (evdConfig.isReference)
1151 {
1152 mOut << " &";
1153 }
1154 if (isUBO)
1155 {
1156 if (type.isArray())
1157 {
1158 for (auto size : type.getArraySizes())
1159 {
1160 mOut << ", " << size;
1161 }
1162 mOut << ">";
1163 }
1164 }
1165 }

1168void GenMetalTraverser::emitFieldDeclaration(const TField &field,
1169 const TStructure &parent,
1170 FieldAnnotationIndices &annotationIndices)
1171{
1172 const TType &type = *field.type();
1173 const TBasicType basic = type.getBasicType();
1174
1175 EmitVariableDeclarationConfig evdConfig;
1176 evdConfig.emitPostQualifier = true;
1177 evdConfig.disableStructSpecifier = true;
1178 evdConfig.isPacked = mSymbolEnv.isPacked(field);
1179 evdConfig.isUBO = mSymbolEnv.isUBO(field);
1180 evdConfig.isPointer = mSymbolEnv.isPointer(field);
1181 evdConfig.isReference = mSymbolEnv.isReference(field);
1182 emitVariableDeclaration(VarDecl(field), evdConfig);
1183
1184 const TQualifier qual = type.getQualifier();
1185 switch (qual)
1186 {
1187 case TQualifier::EvqFlatIn:
1188 if (mPipelineStructs.fragmentIn.external == &parent)
1189 {
1190 mOut << " [[flat]]";
1191 TranslatorMetalReflection *reflection =
1192 ((sh::TranslatorMetalDirect *)&mCompiler)->getTranslatorMetalReflection();
1193 reflection->hasFlatInput = true;
1194 }
1195 break;
1196
1197 case TQualifier::EvqFragmentOut:
1198 case TQualifier::EvqFragData:
1199 if (mPipelineStructs.fragmentOut.external == &parent)
1200 {
1201 if ((type.isVector() &&
1202 (basic == TBasicType::EbtInt || basic == TBasicType::EbtUInt ||
1203 basic == TBasicType::EbtFloat)) ||
1204 type.getQualifier() == EvqFragData)
1205 {
1206 // TODO:
1207 // This is not correct in general and needs a reimplementation.
1208 // In GLSL 3.0, We can't always assume this is going to be a safe index.
1209 // See 4.3.8.2
1210 // https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenGL/specs/es/3.0/GLSL_ES_Specification_3.00.pdf
1211 size_t index = annotationIndices.color++;
1212 mOut << " [[color(" << index << ")]]";
1213 }
1214 }
1215 break;
1216
1217 case TQualifier::EvqFragDepth:
1218 mOut << " [[depth(any)]]";
1219 break;
1220
1221 case TQualifier::EvqSampleMask:
1222 mOut << " [[sample_mask, function_constant(" << sh::TranslatorMetalDirect::GetCoverageMaskEnabledConstName() << ")]]";
1223 break;
1224
1225 default:
1226 break;
1227 }

1230static std::map<Name, size_t> BuildExternalAttributeIndexMap(
1231 const TCompiler &compiler,
1232 const PipelineScoped<TStructure> &structure)
1233{
1234 ASSERT(structure.isTotallyFull());
1235
1236 const auto &shaderVars = compiler.getAttributes();
1237 const size_t shaderVarSize = shaderVars.size();
1238 size_t shaderVarIndex = 0;
1239
1240 const auto &externalFields = structure.external->fields();
1241 const size_t externalSize = externalFields.size();
1242 size_t externalIndex = 0;
1243
1244 const auto &internalFields = structure.internal->fields();
1245 const size_t internalSize = internalFields.size();
1246 size_t internalIndex = 0;
1247
1248 // Internal fields are never split. External fields are sometimes split.
1249 ASSERT(externalSize >= internalSize);
1250
1251 // Structures do not contain any inactive fields.
1252 ASSERT(shaderVarSize >= internalSize);
1253
1254 std::map<Name, size_t> externalNameToAttributeIndex;
1255 size_t attributeIndex = 0;
1256
1257 while (internalIndex < internalSize)
1258 {
1259 const TField &internalField = *internalFields[internalIndex];
1260 const Name internalName = Name(internalField);
1261 const TType &internalType = *internalField.type();
1262 while (internalName.rawName() != shaderVars[shaderVarIndex].name &&
1263 internalName.rawName() != shaderVars[shaderVarIndex].mappedName)
1264 {
1265 // This case represents an inactive field.
1266
1267 ++shaderVarIndex;
1268 ASSERT(shaderVarIndex < shaderVarSize);
1269
1270 ++attributeIndex; // TODO: Might need to increment more if shader var type is a matrix.
1271 }
1272
1273 const size_t cols = internalType.isMatrix() ? internalType.getCols() : 1;
1274
1275 for (size_t c = 0; c < cols; ++c)
1276 {
1277 const TField &externalField = *externalFields[externalIndex];
1278 const Name externalName = Name(externalField);
1279 ASSERT(!externalField.type()->isMatrix());
1280
1281 externalNameToAttributeIndex[externalName] = attributeIndex;
1282
1283 ++externalIndex;
1284 ++attributeIndex;
1285 }
1286
1287 ++shaderVarIndex;
1288 ++internalIndex;
1289 }
1290
1291 ASSERT(shaderVarIndex <= shaderVarSize);
1292 ASSERT(externalIndex <= externalSize); // less than if padding was introduced
1293 ASSERT(internalIndex == internalSize);
1294
1295 return externalNameToAttributeIndex;
1296}

1307void GenMetalTraverser::emitUniformBufferDeclaration(const TField &field,
1308 FieldAnnotationIndices &annotationIndices)
1309{
1310 EmitVariableDeclarationConfig evdConfig;
1311 evdConfig.disableStructSpecifier = true;
1312 evdConfig.isUBO = mSymbolEnv.isUBO(field);
1313 evdConfig.isPointer = mSymbolEnv.isPointer(field);
1314 emitVariableDeclaration(VarDecl(field), evdConfig);
1315 mOut << "[[id(" << annotationIndices.attribute << ")]]";
1316

1324 const std::string originalName =
1325 reflection->getOriginalName(structure->uniqueId().get());
1326 reflection->addUniformBufferBinding(originalName, {.bindIndex = annotationIndices.attribute, .arraySize = static_cast<size_t>(arraySize)});
1327
1328 annotationIndices.attribute += arraySize;

1331void GenMetalTraverser::emitStructDeclaration(const TType &type)
1332{
1333 ASSERT(type.getBasicType() == TBasicType::EbtStruct);
1334 ASSERT(type.isStructSpecifier());
1335
1336 mOut << "struct ";
1337 emitBareTypeName(type, {});
1338
1339 mOut << "\n";
1340 emitOpenBrace();
1341
1342 const TStructure &structure = *type.getStruct();
1343 std::map<Name, size_t> fieldToAttributeIndex;
1344 const bool hasAttributeIndices = mPipelineStructs.vertexIn.external == &structure;
1345 const bool hasUniformBufferIndicies = mPipelineStructs.uniformBuffers.external == &structure;
1346 const bool reclaimUnusedAttributeIndices = mCompiler.getShaderVersion() < 300;
1347
1348 if (hasAttributeIndices)
1349 {
1350 fieldToAttributeIndex =
1351 BuildExternalAttributeIndexMap(mCompiler, mPipelineStructs.vertexIn);
1352 }
1353
1354 FieldAnnotationIndices annotationIndices;
1355
1356 for (const TField *field : structure.fields())
1357 {
1358 emitIndentation();
1359 if (hasAttributeIndices)
1360 {
1361 const auto it = fieldToAttributeIndex.find(Name(*field));
1362 if (it == fieldToAttributeIndex.end())
1363 {
1364 ASSERT(field->symbolType() == SymbolType::AngleInternal);
1365 ASSERT(field->name().beginsWith("_"));
1366 ASSERT(angle::EndsWith(field->name().data(), "_pad"));
1367 emitFieldDeclaration(*field, structure, annotationIndices);
1368 }
1369 else
1370 {
1371 ASSERT(field->symbolType() != SymbolType::AngleInternal ||
1372 !field->name().beginsWith("_") ||
1373 !angle::EndsWith(field->name().data(), "_pad"));
1374 if (!reclaimUnusedAttributeIndices)
1375 {
1376 annotationIndices.attribute = it->second;
1377 }
1378 emitAttributeDeclaration(*field, annotationIndices);
1379 }
1380 }
1381 else if(hasUniformBufferIndicies)
1382 {
1383 emitUniformBufferDeclaration(*field, annotationIndices);
1384 }
1385 else
1386 {
1387 emitFieldDeclaration(*field, structure, annotationIndices);
1388 }
1389 mOut << ";\n";
1390 }
1391
1392 if (!mPipelineStructs.matches(structure, true, true))
1393 {
1394 MetalLayoutOfConfig layoutConfig;
1395 layoutConfig.treatSamplersAsTextureEnv = true;
1396 Layout layout = MetalLayoutOf(type, layoutConfig);
1397 size_t pad = (kDefaultStructAlignmentSize - layout.sizeOf) % kDefaultStructAlignmentSize;
1398 if (pad != 0)
1399 {
1400 emitIndentation();
1401 mOut << "char ";
1402 EmitName(mOut, mIdGen.createNewName("pad"));
1403 mOut << "[" << pad << "];\n";
1404 }
1405 }
1406
1407 emitCloseBrace();
1408}

1456 ASSERT(symbolType != SymbolType::Empty || evdConfig.isParameter);
1457 emitOrdinaryVariableDeclaration(decl, evdConfig);

1460
1461 if (evdConfig.emitPostQualifier)

1650bool GenMetalTraverser::visitBinary(Visit, TIntermBinary *binaryNode)
1651{
1652 const TOperator op = binaryNode->getOp();
1653 TIntermTyped &leftNode = *binaryNode->getLeft();
1654 TIntermTyped &rightNode = *binaryNode->getRight();
1655
1656 switch (op)
1657 {
1658 case TOperator::EOpIndexDirectStruct:
1659 case TOperator::EOpIndexDirectInterfaceBlock:
1660 {
1661 const TField &field = getDirectField(leftNode, rightNode);
1662 if (mSymbolEnv.isPointer(field) && mSymbolEnv.isUBO(field)) {
1663 emitOpeningPointerParen();
1664 }
1665 groupedTraverse(leftNode);
1666 if (!mSymbolEnv.isPointer(field))
1667 {
1668 emitClosingPointerParen();
1669 }
1670 mOut << ".";
1671 emitNameOf(field);
1672 }
1673 break;
1674
1675 case TOperator::EOpIndexDirect:
1676 case TOperator::EOpIndexIndirect:
1677 {
1678 TType leftType = leftNode.getType();
1679 groupedTraverse(leftNode);
1680 mOut << "[";
1681 {
1682 mOut << "ANGLE_int_clamp(";
1683 groupedTraverse(rightNode);
1684 mOut << ", 0, ";
1685 if(leftType.isUnsizedArray())
1686 {
1687 groupedTraverse(leftNode);
1688 mOut << ".size()";
1689 }
1690 else
1691 {
1692 int maxSize;
1693 if (leftType.isArray())
1694 {
1695 maxSize = static_cast<int>(leftType.getOutermostArraySize()) - 1;
1696 }
1697 else
1698 {
1699 maxSize = leftType.getNominalSize() - 1;
1700 }
1701 mOut << maxSize;
1702 }
1703 mOut << ")";
1704 }
1705 mOut << "]";
1706 }
1707 break;
1708
1709 default:
1710 {
1711 const TType &resultType = binaryNode->getType();
1712 const TType &leftType = leftNode.getType();
1713 const TType &rightType = rightNode.getType();
1714
1715 if (IsSymbolicOperator(op, resultType, &leftType, &rightType))
1716 {
1717 groupedTraverse(leftNode);
1718 if (op != TOperator::EOpComma)
1719 {
1720 mOut << " ";
1721 }
1722 else
1723 {
1724 emitClosingPointerParen();
1725 }
1726 mOut << GetOperatorString(op, resultType, &leftType, &rightType) << " ";
1727 groupedTraverse(rightNode);
1728 }
1729 else
1730 {
1731 emitClosingPointerParen();
1732 mOut << GetOperatorString(op, resultType, &leftType, &rightType) << "(";
1733 leftNode.traverse(this);
1734 mOut << ", ";
1735 rightNode.traverse(this);
1736 mOut << ")";
1737 }
1738 }
1739 }
1740
1741 return false;
1742}

1748 case TOperator::EOpPostIncrement:
1749 case TOperator::EOpPostDecrement:
1750 return true;

2074bool GenMetalTraverser::visitAggregate(Visit, TIntermAggregate *aggregateNode)
2075{
2076 const TIntermSequence &args = *aggregateNode->getSequence();
2077
2078 auto emitArgList = [&](const char *open, const char *close) {
2079 mOut << open;
2080
2081 bool emitComma = false;
2082 for (TIntermNode *arg : args)
2083 {
2084 if (emitComma)
2085 {
2086 emitClosingPointerParen();
2087 mOut << ", ";
2088 }
2089 emitComma = true;
2090 arg->traverse(this);
2091 }
2092
2093 mOut << close;
2094 };
2095
2096 const TType &retType = aggregateNode->getType();
2097
2098 if (aggregateNode->isConstructor())
2099 {
2100 const bool isStandalone = getParentNode()->getAsBlock();
2101 if (isStandalone)
2102 {
2103 // Prevent constructor from being interpreted as a declaration by wrapping in parens.
2104 // This can happen if given something like:
2105 // int(symbol); // <- This will be treated like `int symbol;`... don't want that.
2106 // So instead emit:
2107 // (int(symbol));
2108 mOut << "(";
2109 }
2110
2111 const EmitTypeConfig etConfig;
2112
2113 if (retType.isArray())
2114 {
2115 emitType(retType, etConfig);
2116 emitArgList("{", "}");
2117 }
2118 else if (retType.getStruct())
2119 {
2120 emitType(retType, etConfig);
2121 emitArgList("{", "}");
2122 }
2123 else
2124 {
2125 emitType(retType, etConfig);
2126 emitArgList("(", ")");
2127 }
2128
2129 if (isStandalone)
2130 {
2131 mOut << ")";
2132 }
2133
2134 return false;
2135 }
2136 else
2137 {
2138 const TOperator op = aggregateNode->getOp();
2139 switch (op)
2140 {
2141 case TOperator::EOpCallFunctionInAST:
2142 case TOperator::EOpCallInternalRawFunction:
2143 {
2144 const TFunction &func = *aggregateNode->getFunction();
2145 emitNameOf(func);
2146 //'@' symbol in name specifices a macro substitution marker.
2147 if(!func.name().contains("@"))
2148 {
2149 emitArgList("(", ")");
2150 }
2151 else
2152 {
2153 mTemporarilyDisableSemicolon = true; //Disable semicolon for macro substitution.
2154 }
2155 return false;
2156 }
2157
2158 case TOperator::EOpCallBuiltInFunction:
2159 {
2160 const TFunction &func = *aggregateNode->getFunction();
2161 auto it = mFuncToName.find(func.name());
2162 ASSERT(it != mFuncToName.end());
2163 EmitName(mOut, it->second);
2164 emitArgList("(", ")");
2165 return false;
2166 }
2167
2168 default:
2169 {
2170 auto getArgType = [&](size_t index) -> const TType * {
2171 if (index < args.size())
2172 {
2173 TIntermTyped *arg = args[index]->getAsTyped();
2174 ASSERT(arg);
2175 return &arg->getType();
2176 }
2177 return nullptr;
2178 };
2179
2180 ASSERT(!args.empty());
2181 const TType *argType0 = getArgType(0);
2182 const TType *argType1 = getArgType(1);
2183 const TType *argType2 = getArgType(2);
2184 ASSERT(argType0);
2185
2186 const char *opName = GetOperatorString(op, retType, argType0, argType1, argType2);
2187
2188 if (IsSymbolicOperator(op, retType, argType0, argType1))
2189 {
2190 switch (args.size())
2191 {
2192 case 1:
2193 {
2194 TIntermNode &operandNode = *aggregateNode->getChildNode(0);
2195 if (IsPostfix(op))
2196 {
2197 mOut << opName;
2198 groupedTraverse(operandNode);
2199 return false;
2200 }
2201 else
2202 {
2203 groupedTraverse(operandNode);
2204 mOut << opName;
2205 return false;
2206 }
2207 }
2208 break;
2209
2210 case 2:
2211 {
2212 TIntermNode &leftNode = *aggregateNode->getChildNode(0);
2213 TIntermNode &rightNode = *aggregateNode->getChildNode(1);
2214 groupedTraverse(leftNode);
2215 mOut << " " << opName << " ";
2216 groupedTraverse(rightNode);
2217 return false;
2218 }
2219 break;
2220
2221 default:
2222 LOGIC_ERROR();
2223 return false;
2224 }
2225 }
2226 else
2227 {
2228 mOut << opName;
2229 emitArgList("(", ")");
2230 return false;
2231 }
2232 }
2233 }
2234 }
2235}

2305bool GenMetalTraverser::visitBlock(Visit, TIntermBlock *blockNode)
2306{
2307 ASSERT(mIndentLevel >= -1);
2308 const bool isGlobalScope = mIndentLevel == -1;
2309 const bool parentIsSwitch = mParentIsSwitch;
2310 mParentIsSwitch = false;
2311
2312 if (isGlobalScope)
2313 {
2314 ++mIndentLevel;
2315 }
2316 else
2317 {
2318 emitOpenBrace();
2319 if (parentIsSwitch)
2320 {
2321 ++mIndentLevel;
2322 }
2323 }
2324
2325 TIntermNode *prevStmtNode = nullptr;
2326
2327 const size_t stmtCount = blockNode->getChildCount();
2328 for (size_t i = 0; i < stmtCount; ++i)
2329 {
2330 TIntermNode &stmtNode = *blockNode->getChildNode(i);
2331
2332 if (isGlobalScope && prevStmtNode && (NewlinePad(*prevStmtNode) || NewlinePad(stmtNode)))
2333 {
2334 mOut << "\n";
2335 }
2336 const bool isCase = stmtNode.getAsCaseNode();
2337 mIndentLevel -= isCase;
2338 emitIndentation();
2339 mIndentLevel += isCase;
2340 stmtNode.traverse(this);
2341 if (RequiresSemicolonTerminator(stmtNode) && !mTemporarilyDisableSemicolon)
2342 {
2343 mOut << ";";
2344 }
2345 mTemporarilyDisableSemicolon = false;
2346 mOut << "\n";
2347
2348 prevStmtNode = &stmtNode;
2349 }
2350
2351 if (isGlobalScope)
2352 {
2353 ASSERT(mIndentLevel == 0);
2354 --mIndentLevel;
2355 }
2356 else
2357 {
2358 if (parentIsSwitch)
2359 {
2360 ASSERT(mIndentLevel >= 1);
2361 --mIndentLevel;
2362 }
2363 emitCloseBrace();
2364 mParentIsSwitch = parentIsSwitch;
2365 }
2366
2367 return false;

2376bool GenMetalTraverser::visitDeclaration(Visit, TIntermDeclaration *declNode)
2377{
2378 ASSERT(declNode->getChildCount() == 1);
2379 TIntermNode &node = *declNode->getChildNode(0);
2380
2381 EmitVariableDeclarationConfig evdConfig;
2382
2383 if (TIntermSymbol *symbolNode = node.getAsSymbolNode())
2384 {
2385 const TVariable &var = symbolNode->variable();
2386 emitVariableDeclaration(VarDecl(var), evdConfig);
2387 }
2388 else if (TIntermBinary *initNode = node.getAsBinaryNode())
2389 {
2390 ASSERT(initNode->getOp() == TOperator::EOpInitialize);
2391 TIntermSymbol *symbolNode = initNode->getLeft()->getAsSymbolNode();
2392 TIntermTyped *valueNode = initNode->getRight()->getAsTyped();
2393 ASSERT(symbolNode && valueNode);
2394
2395 if (getRootNode() == getParentBlock())
2396 {
2397 // DeferGlobalInitializers should have turned non-const global initializers into
2398 // deferred initializers. Note that variables marked as EvqGlobal can be treated as
2399 // EvqConst in some ANGLE code but not actually have their qualifier actually changed to
2400 // EvqConst. Thus just assume all EvqGlobal are actually EvqConst for all code run after
2401 // DeferGlobalInitializers.
2402 mOut << "constant ";
2403 }
2404
2405 const TVariable &var = symbolNode->variable();
2406 const Name varName(var);
2407
2408 if (ExpressionContainsName(varName, *valueNode))
2409 {
2410 mRenamedSymbols[&var] = mIdGen.createNewName(varName);
2411 }
2412
2413 emitVariableDeclaration(VarDecl(var), evdConfig);
2414 mOut << " = ";
2415 groupedTraverse(*valueNode);
2416 }
2417 else
2418 {
2419 LOGIC_ERROR();
2420 }
2421
2422 return false;
2423}

2425bool GenMetalTraverser::visitLoop(Visit, TIntermLoop *loopNode)
2426{
2427 const TLoopType loopType = loopNode->getType();
2428
2429 switch (loopType)
2430 {
2431 case TLoopType::ELoopFor:
2432 return visitForLoop(loopNode);
2433 case TLoopType::ELoopWhile:
2434 return visitWhileLoop(loopNode);
2435 case TLoopType::ELoopDoWhile:
2436 return visitDoWhileLoop(loopNode);
2437 }
2438}

2440bool GenMetalTraverser::visitForLoop(TIntermLoop *loopNode)
2441{
2442 ASSERT(loopNode->getType() == TLoopType::ELoopFor);
2443
2444 TIntermNode *initNode = loopNode->getInit();
2445 TIntermTyped *condNode = loopNode->getCondition();
2446 TIntermTyped *exprNode = loopNode->getExpression();
2447 TIntermBlock *bodyNode = loopNode->getBody();
2448 ASSERT(bodyNode);
2449
2450 mOut << "for (";
2451
2452 if (initNode)
2453 {
2454 initNode->traverse(this);
2455 }
2456 else
2457 {
2458 mOut << " ";
2459 }
2460
2461 mOut << "; ";
2462
2463 if (condNode)
2464 {
2465 condNode->traverse(this);
2466 }
2467
2468 mOut << "; ";
2469
2470 if (exprNode)
2471 {
2472 exprNode->traverse(this);
2473 }
2474
2475 mOut << ")\n";
2476
2477 bodyNode->traverse(this);
2478
2479 return false;
2480}

2482bool GenMetalTraverser::visitWhileLoop(TIntermLoop *loopNode)
2483{
2484 ASSERT(loopNode->getType() == TLoopType::ELoopWhile);
2485
2486 TIntermNode *initNode = loopNode->getInit();
2487 TIntermTyped *condNode = loopNode->getCondition();
2488 TIntermTyped *exprNode = loopNode->getExpression();
2489 TIntermBlock *bodyNode = loopNode->getBody();
2490 ASSERT(condNode && bodyNode);
2491 ASSERT(!initNode && !exprNode);
2492
2493 emitIndentation();
2494 mOut << "while (";

2496 mOut << ")\n";
2497 bodyNode->traverse(this);
2498
2499 return false;
2500}

2525bool GenMetalTraverser::visitBranch(Visit, TIntermBranch *branchNode)
2526{
2527 const TOperator flowOp = branchNode->getFlowOp();
2528 TIntermTyped *exprNode = branchNode->getExpression();
2529
2530 emitIndentation();
2531
2532 switch (flowOp)
2533 {
2534 case TOperator::EOpKill:
2535 {
2536 ASSERT(exprNode == nullptr);
2537 mOut << "metal::discard_fragment()";
2538 }
2539 break;
2540
2541 case TOperator::EOpReturn:
2542 {
2543 if(isTraversingVertexMain)
2544 {
2545 mOut << "#if TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_ENABLED\n";
2546 emitIndentation();
2547 mOut << "return;\n";
2548 emitIndentation();
2549 mOut << "#else\n";
2550 emitIndentation();
2551 }
2552 mOut << "return";
2553 if (exprNode)
2554 {
2555 mOut << " ";
2556 exprNode->traverse(this);
2557 mOut << ";";
2558 }
2559 if(isTraversingVertexMain)
2560 {
2561 mOut << "\n";
2562 emitIndentation();
2563 mOut << "#endif\n";
2564 mTemporarilyDisableSemicolon = true;
2565 }
2566 }
2567 break;
2568
2569 case TOperator::EOpBreak:
2570 {
2571 ASSERT(exprNode == nullptr);
2572 mOut << "break";
2573 }
2574 break;
2575
2576 case TOperator::EOpContinue:
2577 {
2578 ASSERT(exprNode == nullptr);
2579 mOut << "continue";
2580 }
2581 break;
2582
2583 default:
2584 {
2585 LOGIC_ERROR();
2586 }
2587 }
2588
2589 return false;
2590}

2592static size_t emitMetalCallCount = 0;
2593
2594bool sh::EmitMetal(TCompiler &compiler,
2595 TIntermBlock &root,
2596 IdGen &idGen,
2597 const PipelineStructs &pipelineStructs,
2598 const Invariants &invariants,
2599 SymbolEnv &symbolEnv,
2600 const ProgramPreludeConfig &ppc)
2601{
2602 TInfoSinkBase &out = compiler.getInfoSink().obj;
2603
2604 {
2605 ++emitMetalCallCount;
2606 auto filenameProto = readStringEnvVar("GMD_FIXED_EMIT");
2607 if (!filenameProto.empty())
2608 {
2609 if (filenameProto != "/dev/null")
2610 {
2611 auto tryOpen = [&](char const *ext) {
2612 auto filename = filenameProto;
2613 filename += std::to_string(emitMetalCallCount);
2614 filename += ".";
2615 filename += ext;
2616 return fopen(filename.c_str(), "rb");
2617 };
2618 FILE *file = tryOpen("metal");
2619 if (!file)
2620 {
2621 file = tryOpen("cpp");
2622 }
2623 ASSERT(file);
2624
2625 fseek(file, 0, SEEK_END);
2626 size_t fileSize = ftell(file);
2627 fseek(file, 0, SEEK_SET);
2628
2629 std::vector<char> buff;
2630 buff.resize(fileSize + 1);
2631 fread(buff.data(), fileSize, 1, file);
2632 buff.back() = '\0';
2633
2634 fclose(file);
2635
2636 out << buff.data();
2637 }
2638
2639 return true;
2640 }
2641 }
2642
2643 out << "\n\n";
2644
2645 if (!EmitProgramPrelude(root, out, ppc))
2646 {
2647 return false;
2648 }
2649
2650 {
2651#if defined(ANGLE_ENABLE_ASSERTS)
2652 DebugSink outWrapper(out, readBoolEnvVar("GMD_STDOUT"));
2653 outWrapper.watch(readStringEnvVar("GMD_WATCH_STRING"));
2654#else
2655 TInfoSinkBase &outWrapper = out;
2656#endif
2657 GenMetalTraverser gen(compiler, outWrapper, idGen, pipelineStructs, invariants, symbolEnv);
2658 root.traverse(&gen);
2659 }
2660
2661 out << "\n";
2662
2663 return true;
2664}
